 :tx/rationale "INV-LAYOUT-006: Mechanistic C1 Enforcement — Transaction files are immutable after write. IMPLEMENTED in layout.rs. Four defense layers: (1) File permissions 0o444 after write — blocks direct writes and echo >. (2) Directory sticky bit 1755 on txns/ and shard dirs — blocks sed -i rename trick from non-owner processes. (3) BLAKE3 hash verification on every read (INV-LAYOUT-005) — catches any tamper that bypasses layers 1-2. (4) Automatic quarantine: tampered files renamed to .edn.corrupt and excluded from future loads. Applied on: write_tx(), write_tx_no_invalidate(), seal_existing_txns() (retroactive), load_store() (migration on first load), init() (new stores). FALSIFICATION: This invariant is violated if any .edn file in txns/ can be modified by a non-root process after it was written by braid, AND the modification is not detected and quarantined on the next load."
